==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''ex-'' + ''hortor, hortari'' "to encourage."

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# The act or practice of [[exhort]]ing; the act of inciting to laudable deeds; incitement to that which is good or commendable.
# Language intended to incite and encourage; advice; counsel; admonition.

